quran[17]{c,v,t,f}:
  52,15,"Is this [punishment] magic, or do you not see?",""
  52,16,"Burn in it, whether you bear it patiently or impatiently, it makes no difference to you<sup>8</sup>; you are recompensed only for what you used to do.”","[8] He who is patient during afflictions in the life of this world will be rewarded. As for the Hereafter, suffering patiently in Hell will not bring any reward or benefit."
  52,17,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and bliss,",""
  52,18,"enjoying what their Lord has given them, and their Lord protected them from the punishment of the Blazing Fire.",""
  52,19,"“Eat and drink pleasantly for what you used to do,",""
  52,20,"reclining on couches all lined up”. And We will marry them to houris with wide beautiful eyes.",""
  52,21,"As for those who believe and their offspring follow them in faith, We will cause their offspring to join them, and will not detract anything from [the reward of] their deeds. Everyone will be accountable for what he earned<sup>9</sup>.","[9] i.e., None will be held responsible for the burden of another."
  52,22,"And We will provide them with whatever fruit and meat they desire.",""
  52,23,"They will pass around to one another a glass [of pure wine] which does not lead to idle talk or sin.",""
  52,24,"They will be served by their servant boys, as if they were well-protected pearls.",""
  52,25,"They will turn to one another with questions<sup>10</sup>.","[10] They will probably ask one another about their worldly lives and what led them to Paradise."
  52,26,"They will say, “Before this, we used to be in awe [of Allah] when we were living among our people.",""
  52,27,"Therefore Allah conferred favor upon us and protected us from the punishment of the Scorching Fire.",""
  52,28,"Indeed, we used to call upon Him before. He is indeed the Most Kind, the Most Merciful.”",""
  52,29,"So keep exhorting [O Prophet], for you are not, by the grace of your Lord, a soothsayer or a madman.",""
  52,30,"Or do they say: “He is a poet for whom we await a misfortune<sup>11</sup>”?","[11] i.e., inevitable death or so."
  52,31,"Say, “Wait, I too am waiting with you.”",""
